The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Songs chase sun

 PAUL ECCLESTON

 London, July 7: The Live Earth concerts spanning seven continents with an audience of more than 2 billion people one in three on the planet are under way.

 The first concert began in Sydney at 1.10am (5.40am IST) and they will run until 4am (8.30am IST) tomorrow in New York.

 In between, the music chased the sun from east to west, with concerts in Tokyo, Shanghai, Johannesburg, Hamburg and London. Later tonight, it was to touch Rio de Janeiro, where one million may turn up for the free concert on the Copacabana Beach. In London, 60,000 people had paid 55 each to be at the concert in the new Wembley Stadium.

 The concerts feature 150 of the worlds top bands and artists and were being broadcast in 120 countries. All carried the message that the Earth has to wake up now if it is to meet the challenges posed by global warming.

 The aim is to get millions of people committed to changing their lifestyles and demanding change from their own governments.

 London will have Madonna, the Red Hot Chili Peppers, Kasabian, Keane and Snow Patrol. New York gets the newly-reformed Police, Bon Jovi, KT Tunstall and the Smashing Pumpkins.

